This marker file declares that this repo IS dream-warden running in standalone mode.
dream_dir() in bin/dream_lib.py checks for this file at repo root and resolves to
the repo root rather than looking for a nested .workflow/_dream/ path.

When dream-warden is installed into another project (at .workflow/_dream/), this file
lives at .workflow/_dream/.dream-standalone — NOT at the project root — so it does
not trigger standalone mode for the host project.

Delete or rename this file only if you intend to install this copy inside another
project and want the installed-mode path resolution to apply.
